Package com.fortify.processrunner.processor

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IProcessor
    This interface defines processors that can perform arbitrary tasks when the IProcessor.process(Phase, Context) method is invoked.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractCompositeProcessor
    This abstract IProcessor implementation provides support for invoking a list of individual IProcessor instances.
    AbstractProcessor
    This abstract IProcessor implementation allows subclasses to implement only specific processing phases by overriding the AbstractProcessor.preProcess(Context), AbstractProcessor.process(Context) and/or AbstractProcessor.postProcess(Context) methods respectively.
    AbstractProcessorBuildObjectMapFromGroupedObjects
    This abstract class allows for building an object map from grouped objects.
    AbstractProcessorBuildObjectMapsFromGroupedObjects
    This abstract class allows for building a object maps from grouped objects.
    AbstractProcessorGroupByExpressions
    This IProcessor implementation allows for collecting and grouping data stored in the Context during the Phase#PROCESS phase.
    CompositeOrderedProcessor
    This CompositeProcessor implementation will dynamically re-order the list of IProcessor instances based on the current value of the Ordered.getOrder() method for each IProcessor, whenever the CompositeOrderedProcessor.getProcessors() method is called.
    CompositeProcessor
    This IProcessor implementation allows a list of individual IProcessor instances to be configured using the constructor or CompositeProcessor.addProcessors(IProcessor...) method.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    IProcessor.Phase
    Enumeration describing the available processing phases.
